/PGALTERNATIVE AMIDOT/XX730/XX/PR

/KAA SHORT AMIDAH/XX/PR

They say weòre supposed to be in a palace./PR

So we bow and take certain steps/PR

as the prescribed supplication/PR

drops from our lips./PR

But what do we really know/PR

of castles and kings?/PR

My kitchen faucet constantly leaks/PR

and the kidsò faces/PR

usually need cleaning./PR

If a door opened to a real palace,/PR

Iòd probably forget/PR

and carry in a load of groceries./PR

/PR

No, the door we stand in front of/PR

when the /ITAmidah/XX begins is silence./PR

And when we open it/PR

and step through,/PR

we arrive in our hearts./PR

Mineòs not a fancy place,/PR

no jewels, no throne,/PR

certainly not fit for a king./PR

But in that small chamber,/PR

for just a few moments on Sabbath,/PR

God and I can roll up our sleeves,/PR

put some schnapps out on the table,/PR

sit down together, and finally talk./PR

Thatòs palace enough for me./PR

Syd Lieberman/XX/PR

