/KASong of the Sabbath / Das Gezang fon Shabes/XX/PR

I quarreled with kings till the Sabbath,/PR

I fought with the six kings/PR

of the six days of the week./PR

/PR

Sunday they took away my sleep./PR

Monday they scattered my salt./PR

And on the third day, my God,/PR

they threw out my bread: whips flashed/PR

across my face. The fourth day/PR

they caught my dove, my flying dove,/PR

and slaughtered it./PR

It was like that till Friday morning./PR

/PR

This is my whole week,/PR

the doveòs flight dying./PI/PR

/PR

/PR

/PR

/PGREADINGS: SHABBAT/XX736/XX/PR

At nightfall Friday/PR

I lit four candles,/PR

and the queen of the Sabbath came to me./PR

Her face lit up the whole world,/PR

and made it all a Sabbath./PR

My scattered salt/PR

shone in its little bowl,/PR

and my dove, my flying dove,/PR

clapped its wings together,/PR

and licked its throat./PR

The Sabbath queen blessed my candles,/PR

and they burned with a pure, clean flame./PR

The light put out the days of the week/PR

and my quarreling with the six kings./PR

/PR

The greenness of the mountains/PR

is the greenness of the Sabbath./PR

The silver of the lake/PR

is the silver of the Sabbath./PR

The singing of the wind/PR

is the singing of the Sabbath./PR

/PR

And my heartòs song/PR

is an eternal Sabbath./PR

Kadia Molodowsky (translated from Yiddish by Jean Valentine)/XX/PR

/PR

/PR

